<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CPT-SPORTS-ON-THE-NET-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NHL.COM BENEFITS FROM RELATIONSHIP WITH ESPN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOMMY CUMMINGS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Followers of the World Wide Web will notice that alliances and
deals between Internet companies are being struck every day.
</P>
<P>
   America Online is merging with Netscape Communications. Yahoo!
is eyeing Broadcast.com. Microsoft and NBC have already spawned
MSNBC.com.
</P>
<P>
   It's also happening in the cybersports world.
</P>
<P>
   ESPN Internet Ventures, a joint venture of Disney's Buena Vista
Internet Group and Infoseek, has become a major player by operating
official sites for the NBA, NFL and NASCAR and ABCNews.com's Bowl
Championship Series and Monday Night Football sites as well as
ESPN.com, the 'Net's most popular sports site.
</P>
<P>
   Yesterday, ESPN Internet Ventures added the NHL in its
expansion.
</P>
<P>
   NHL.com, the league's official site operated by NHL Interactive
CyberEnterprises, entered into a relationship with ESPN Internet
Ventures to develop a co-branded gamecast application and official
fantasy game as well as include NHL video highlights on ESPN.com.
</P>
<P>
   These features will be available through ESPN.com and NHL.com
before the end of the current NHL season and extend through the end
of the 2000-01 NHL season.
</P>
<P>
   So what does all this cyber-mumbo-jumbo mean to the average
NHL.com user?
</P>
<P>
   Plenty.
</P>
<P>
   It means more exposure for NHL.com's better features, especially
those NHL fans who follow the game online.
</P>
<P>
   According to details announced yesterday, ESPN Internet Ventures
will have preferred use of statistics generated from the NHL's Real
Time Scoring System _ meaning the gamecast will have real-time
depictions of all NHL games.
</P>
<P>
   Also, the official fantasy game will make use of the real-time
scoring system. NHL.com plans to feature a basic game free of
charge and a more sophisticated game that is fee-based.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps, best of all for NHL.com, it becomes part of the ESPN
network, meaning that the site will be linked from all of the main
ESPN.com pages. ESPN.com receives the most traffic of any
sports-related site, according to Media Metrix, which measures
online traffic.
</P>
<P>
   Tom Richardson, general manager of NHL Interactive
CyberEnterprises, said the agreement gives the league a chance to
take advantage of ESPN's assets.
</P>
<P>
   ``It will also help raise the profile of NHL.com and spur
further growth this year and beyond,'' Richardson said in a news
release.
</P>
<P>
   The agreement also opens the door to more integration of NHL
content with ESPN's, said Steve Zales, senior vice president and
general manager of ESPN Internet Ventures.
</P>
<P>
   NHL.com does well on its own with live audio broadcasts of NHL
games, the latest in league news, licensed merchandise and video
highlights.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE RIGHT TRACK: Phil Murray, a volunteer track coach at
Boswell High School in Saginaw, Texas, has seen the popularity of
his Texas Track &AMP; Field Online (www.texastrack.com) vault in the
past few months.
</P>
<P>
   Murray said his site, a comprehensive clearinghouse of all
things related to track and field in Texas, received 2.1 million
hits last year, and he expects more this year, including about
500,000 this month. The increased traffic meant Murray had to move
his site to a service provider with more space.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't realize when I started how much the entire world
looks to Texas as a mecca for the sport, especially at the high
school level,'' Murray said.
</P>
<P>
   Besides information about the hundreds of meets, Murray has
added interactivity featuring a chat room and discussion forum and
a survey.
</P>
<P>
   NFL AS A RESOURCE: The NFL plans to launch a site designed to
support and recognize high school and youth football, according to
a news release by NFL Charities. The site, which is scheduled to be
launched in mid-August, is expected to include coaching
information, officiating instruction, health and nutrition
information and direction on college scholarships.
</P>
<P>
   (Tommy Cummings writes about the Internet for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. You can contact him at (817) 390-7397. E-mail:
dragon(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the Star-Telegram's online
services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
