<HEADLINE>
MAVERICKS SIGN 7-3 TEEN-AGER FROM CROATIA
</HEADLINE>
 NOTES-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ The Mavericks grew taller and younger yesterday when
they signed Bruno Sundov, a 7-foot-3 center from Split, Croatia.
</P>
<P>
   A second-round draft choice by the Mavericks in the last NBA
draft, Sundov, 19, will begin the season on the injured list
because of a fractured wrist. Sundov scored eight points in 10
minutes against a group of high-school all-stars from the United
States in the Hoop Summit game.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is a project,'' Mavericks coach Don Nelson said of Sundov.
``He's several years away, but we're taking this opportunity to
sign him now.
</P>
<P>
   ``He will basically just be in our development program, and he
will work with our personal trainer, Bill Peterson. That'll give us
our summer program to work with him and training camp next year,
and then we'll see.''
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks had to sign Sundov this season, or else he could
have re-entered the next draft.
</P>
<P>
   Nelson said Sundov has put on about 20 pounds since the draft,
and now weighs approximately 220. He might be even bigger now,
according to Nelson, who said Sundov went to Bob's Steak and
Chophouse in Dallas and ate a 28-ounce steak.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was eye-balling mine,'' Nelson said, laughing.
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks also moved injured point guard Robert Pack to the
active roster to make room for Sundov on the injured list.
</P>
<P>
   Pack, who is recovering from a torn right hamstring, is not
slated to return to action for at least another three weeks. SESAY
OUT OF CAST
</P>
<P>
   Rookie forward Ansu Sesay had the cast removed from his
fractured right foot yesterday and replaced it with a walking boot.
</P>
<P>
   He will start rehabilitating the foot today.
</P>
<P>
   ``I need to get my movement back in it,'' Sesay said. ``But I
can't start running for another month.''
</P>
<P>
   Sesay fractured the foot during training camp and will miss the
season. He was a second-round draft pick out of Mississippi.
BRIEFLY
</P>
<P>
   _ Center John `Hot Rod' Williams missed Monday night's game
because he had the flu.
</P>
<P>
   _ With Erick Strickland in the starting lineup last night for
the first time this season, the Mavericks have used 11 starting
lineups this season.
</P>
<P>
   _ Former Mavericks general manager Norm Sonju attended last
night's game.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mavs Man, the Mavericks' popular mascot, limped off the court
holding his right leg after dunking during a third-quarter timeout.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
