   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The Supreme Court dealt affirmative
action another blow Monday, continuing the trend of giving up on
efforts to remedy bias through racial and gender preferences. But
we are not yet a gender-or color-blind nation. Only last week the
Massachusetts Institute of Technology confessed that female
professors there suffer from pervasive discrimination. By MARIANNE
MEANS.
</P>
<P>
