<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR; 
``Experts say this fighting in Yugoslavia could drag on for six
months with no real winner. Kind of like a Don King fight.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Wacky Jack ``The Suicide'' Kevorkian continuing to represent
himself in his latest trial. Just when you thought his reputation
couldn't get any worse, he becomes a lawyer.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Monica Lewinsky wants to start a singing career. Maybe that's
what she was doing in the oval office, strengthening her vocal
chords.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Did everyone watch the Oscar's? I watched the whole thing. I
didn't watch it by myself. My wife and I took turns, like
long-distance truck drivers. I'd sleep for a while, she'd watch and
I'd wake up, she'd nap for a while.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I love Roberto Benigni. He's waving his arms. He's jumping up
and down. He's like a thinking man's Richard Simmons.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``James Hoffa, son of the famous union boss Jimmy Hoffa, was
sworn in as the new president of the teamster union yesterday. He
would've been sworn in sooner, but they were all on break.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Australia is being pounded by a new storm. This one's called
Cyclone Vance. What kind of a name is that? Sounds like some kind
of male porno star.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Jesse Jackson announced that he would not run for president.
Apparently he was unable to come up with a word that rhymes with
millennium.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN' &LR; 
``According to the New York Post, people sitting near Whitney
Houston at the Oscars became really annoyed because she kept
yelling `Amen.' It must have gotten pretty bad because at one point
God yelled, `Shut up!'''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Dr. Kevorkian's trial started today and he's acting as his own
lawyer. Apparently, there was one awkward moment this morning when
Kevorkian asked to approach the bench and the judge said, `No,
really, I'm fine.'''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``The Pope announced that he's going to say mass in Israel next
year. When asked why, the Pope said, `I want to perform in front of
crowds that haven't heard any of my material before.'''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``In a recent interview, Bob Dole says his TV commercials for
Viagra won't hurt his wife's campaign for president. He also says
the Viagra commercials won't hurt his campaign to nail Heather
Locklear.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Jesse Jackson told reporters that he is not planning on
running for President next year. He says the job has changed a lot
and he doesn't think he can handle the pressures of dating.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``This week, supermodel Kate Moss appears nude in the British
version of `Vogue' magazine. Unfortunately, you can't see much of
her because she's covered by the magazine's staple.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``A mother in Florida is in trouble for taking her two-year-old
with her while she was breaking into homes. When asked why she did
it, she said, `I thought it was that `Bring Your Daughters to Work
Day.'''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Mike Tyson's sister says that Mike Tyson is training in prison
so he can get back in the ring the second he's released. In a
related story, Don King has already declared Tyson the winner of
that fight.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``It was reported today that Calista Flockhart and Ben Stiller
are dating. When asked about it Stiller said, `It's no big deal.
She's just had me over a couple of times for coffee and a
raisin.'''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Today is the one-year anniversary of the Food and Drug
Administration's approval of the Viagra pill. It's also the oneyear
anniversary of Elizabeth Dole not getting any sleep.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Dr. Kevorkian rested his defense without the help of witnesses
because the judge wouldn't allow Kevorkian to call the witnesses he
wanted. Mainly because Kevorkian wanted witnesses to put one hand
on the Bible and the other hand in a toaster.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``This week, a group of college students from the Midwest
decided to spend their Spring Break in Washington to help the
homeless. Actually they weren't that effective because all they did
was help the homeless organize a wet T-shirt contest.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Producers of the Oscar-winning movie `Life is Beautiful'
announced they are going to re-dub the Italian film into English.
Not only that, the producers of the Oscars said they're going to
re-dub Roberto Benigni's English into English.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Today, the Russian parliament announced they're considering
impeaching Boris Yeltsin. Apparently, if the impeachment goes
through, they're going to have the bouncer throw him out of the
Kremlin.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``In Florida, officials at a local high school have decided to
allow a teenage boy to attend his senior prom in drag. Not only
that, he and his date have a good chance of being chosen queen and
queen.''  &QL;
</P>
