<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   MCCOY-COLUMN _ FORT MYERS, Fla. _ An American League scout sat
behind the screen at City of Palms Park, casually asking questions
about the Cincinnati Reds. ``How many pitchers will they carry?''
the man asked. Ten. ``Ten? Ten? How can they do that? Their bullpen
arms will be dangling like cooked spaghetti strands by May,'' he
said. ``I mean, check out their starters. Other than Brett Tomko,
they don't have guys who will go more than five innings.'' This is
an astute observer, a guy worth the price of his straw hat and
sunscreen. (McCoy, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-SPIKES _ The soft-spike trend of two years ago has turned
into a non-metal spikes mandate on most golf courses in Georgia.
But there are greenskeepers who think it was much ado about
nothing. Are the greens in better shape because of the move to soft
spikes? And how have the pros, who play in Atlanta this week in the
BellSouth, responded. What are they wearing? (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BCK-FINALFOUR-FOLO _ NCAA men's championship folo. (Barnhart,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
