<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, March 31 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SCOTCH-GALORE (Los Angeles) _ You can find about 550 brands of
single-malt scotch whisky at Wine &AMP; Liquor Depot _ ranging in price
from about $16 to $7,000 and in age from relatively young to
venerable. It's enough variety in a decidedly esoteric niche market
to give store owner Howard Meister bragging rights to the largest
supply of single malt in America, or maybe even the world. By
Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   PACIFIC-IPO (Newbury Park, Calif.) _ Pacific Softworks Inc. in
Newbury Park, a developer of Internet-related software, has filed
to go public. By Deborah Adamson.
