inquiries, call Eddie Ibardolasa at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BBO-CACTUS (Tempe, Ariz.) _ ``If you build it, they will come,''
was the catch phrase from the movie ``Field of Dreams.'' The Cactus
League has made it work in the real world, only there are no corn
fields to be found here in the Arizona desert. The Cactus League is
booming, attracting major league teams faster than you can say
Dodgertown. Ten of the major league's 30 teams conduct spring
training here, with more expected to come, possibly even the
Dodgers. 
By Joe Haakenson/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
RAC-MODESTI-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Just call it jockeying for
position. Trainer Bob Baffert, for the Santa Anita Derby, replaced
jockey Chris McCarron with Gary Stevens on Monday. On Tuesday,
Baffert and McCarron's agent, Scotty McClellan, got into a shoving
match and now the issue is before the track stewards. 
By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKC-BASKETBALL-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ College basketball column,
wrapping up NCAA Tournament. 
By Jon Wilner. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-CLIPPERS-ROCKETS (Los Angeles) _ The Los Angeles Clippers face
the Houston Rockets at 7:30 p.m. PST. 
By Randy Hill/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 
SOC-CIENFUEGOS (Los Angeles) _ Rarely do people side with athletes
involved in contract disputes, but in Mauricio Cienfuegos' case,
the Los Angeles Galaxy should show him the money. 
By Fred J. Robledo/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERNOTES (Vero Beach, Fla.) _ Los Angeles Dodgers notebook
from spring training. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
FBC-USCNOTES (Los Angeles) _ USC football notebook. 
By Scott Wolf. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 

