<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Beijing) _ Dampening hopes for a quick agreement on
China's entry into the World Trade Organization, American officials
said Tuesday that ``difficult and complex issues remain across all
areas of trade'' after a visit to China by the White House trade
representative. By Erik Eckholm.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
