   MEDICARE-ECONOMY (Washington) _ In a report that could give
Congress an excuse to put off overhauling the federal health
insurance and retirement benefits programs, the Treasury Department
says the robust economy and already enacted changes will extend the
solvency of Medicare by seven years and Social Security by two
years. By BENNETT ROTH.
