contact Emily Kelley at (713) 220-7674 or 6845. 
 
NATION 
FEN-PHEN _ (HOUSTON) A three-judge panel in Harris County, Texas,
on Monday became the first court in the nation to disallow evidence
that the ``phen'' part of the ``fen-phen'' diet drug combination
has helped cause heart defects. By RON NISSIMOV. 
 
FEATURES 
BIRD-TRAIL _ (GALVESTON, Texas) A colony of 500 white pelicans
forms a flotilla, bobbing gently on the waves that lap the shore of
the Bolivar mud flats, a thin strip of land on Texas' Gulf coast.
Up to 10,000 birds, representing 50 species, congregate on this
tranquil 500-acre Galveston Bay marsh. It's the Houston Audubon
Society's Shorebird Sanctuary and is one of 125 sites listed on a
new map showing where to ``bird watch'' in the Houston area. By
CINDY HORSWELL 
 
