   (NYT10) BOSTON -- March 30, 1999 -- SEDER-ARTIFACT-BOS, 3-30 --
Saul Touster with the original copy of a 1946 Haggadah, a Passover
prayer book put together by Jewish survivors of the Holocaust.
Touster, 73, professor emeritus of law and social policy at
Brandeis University, vowed to learn the book's story and to
preserve it. The Haggadah was published by the U.S. Army and used
at a Seder in Munich on the first Passover after the fall of Nazi
Germany. (Tom Herde/Boston Globe Photo) *LITE
</P>
