<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, MARCH 31
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-INTERNET-VOLUME-NYT (moved on Sunday, Mar. 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Mar. 28,
about efforts to place a value on the traffic volume of various
World Wide Web sites, misstated the amount of money raised by
iVillage.com in its recent stock offering. The company raised $87.6
million, not $292 million, which was the value of the shares at the
end of the first trading day.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SONY-MGM-AD-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Monday, Mar. 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Mar. 29,
about a dispute between Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc. and Sony Pictures
Entertainment over the James Bond movie franchise, described the
ownership of MGM incorrectly. It is a publicly traded company, of
which 90 percent is owned by Kirk Kerkorian's Tracinda Corporation.
</P>
</TEXT>
